  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chief Technology Officer (CTO)",
  "description": "<h3>Technology Strategy & Governance</h3><ul><li><p>Define and execute the company’s technology vision and roadmap in alignment with healthcare business objectives.</p></li><li><p>Ensure technology initiatives support patient care, clinical outcomes, and operational excellence.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate emerging healthcare technologies (e.g., telemedicine, AI, data analytics, interoperability standards).</p></li><li><p>Provide strategic technology guidance to executive leadership and the board.</p></li></ul><h3>Healthcare Systems & Digital Solutions</h3><ul><li><p>Oversee development, integration, and maintenance of healthcare systems and patient portals.</p></li><li><p>Ensure interoperability between clinical, operational, and financial systems.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with clinical and operations teams to translate healthcare needs into technology solutions.</p></li><li><p>Support digital health initiatives, including telehealth, mobile health applications, and data-driven care models.</p></li></ul><h3>Data Security, Privacy & Compliance</h3><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with healthcare regulations and standards (e.g., HIPAA, PDPA, GDPR, HL7, ISO 27001, local MOH requirements).</p></li><li><p>Establish and enforce cybersecurity, data privacy, and patient data protection frameworks.</p></li><li><p>Oversee disaster recovery, business continuity, and incident response planning.</p></li><li><p>Ensure ethical and responsible use of healthcare data and technology.</p></li></ul><h3>Infrastructure & IT Operations</h3><ul><li><p>Ensure reliability, performance, and scalability of IT infrastructure and cloud platforms.</p></li><li><p>Oversee IT operations, system availability, and vendor-managed services.</p></li><li><p>Implement best practices for DevOps, system monitoring, and performance optimization.</p></li></ul><h3>Leadership & Team Development</h3><ul><li><p>Build, lead, and mentor high-performing engineering, IT, and health informatics teams.</p></li><li><p>Foster a culture of innovation, accountability, and continuous improvement.</p></li><li><p>Define team structure, roles, and professional development paths.</p></li><li><p>Set performance goals and KPIs aligned with healthcare outcomes and service quality.</p></li></ul><h3>Budgeting & Vendor Management</h3><ul><li><p>Manage the technology budget with a focus on cost efficiency and value creation.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate, select, and manage healthcare technology vendors and partners.</p></li><li><p>Negotiate contracts and ensure vendors meet compliance and service standards.</p></li></ul>",
